<abstract>
<p>Manufacturing managers are continuously trying to decrease production costs by focusing on activities and resource costs besides the relevant cost drivers. Through a case study, we show how to implement activity-based costing and time-driven activity-based costing techniques in a production planning problem environment. The results can significantly reduce production costs and improve manufacturing profitability index.</p>
</abstract>
